inlineContent.text: When you want to store a secret such as a password or cryptographic key, you package it as a keychain item. Along with the data itself, you provide a set of publicly visible attributes both to control the itemâ€™s accessibility and to make it searchable. As shown in Figure 1, keychain services handles data encryption and storage (including data attributes) in a keychain, which is an encrypted database stored on disk. Later, authorized processes use keychain services to find the item and decrypt its data.
